a 1181","Abt 1191":"circa 1191","Smolensk, Smolensk, Russia":"Smolensk, Smolensky Rayon, Smolensk, Russia, Sowjetunion"},"en":{"1167–":"1167–Deceased","1154–1223":"1154–1223","1175–Male":"1175–Deceased","1177–Male":"1177–Deceased","1181–Male":"1181–Deceased","1183–1245":"1183–1245","1185–Female":"1185–Deceased","1187–1220":"1187–1220","1189–Female":"1189–Deceased","1191–Female":"1191–Deceased","1167–Female":"1167–Deceased","1220":"1220","1187":"1187","1154":"1154","1175":"1175","1185":"1185","1183":"1183","1181":"1181","1191":"1191","ABT 1183":"about 1183","ABT 1185":"about 1185","ABT 1175":"about 1175","ABT 1187":"about 1187","ABT 1177":"about 1177","1245":"1245","1223":"1223","1167":"1167","ABT 1189":"about 1189","1189":"1189","1177":"1177","ABT 1181":"about 1181","Abt 1191":"about 1191","Smolensk, Smolensk, Russia":"Smolensk, Smolensky Rayon, Smolensk, Russia, Soviet Union","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Романович","type":"LAST","attribution":"Familio name data.","meanings":["The last name of Belarusian origin derives from the baptismal name Roman (Latin Romanus, from Greek Romaike meaning «Rome resident, from Rome»). It is formed from the patronymic suffix -ovich.","The last name is widespread in Belarus. In Russia, it most frequently appears in Moscow and its suburbs, St. Petersburg, the Krasnodar Territory, the Rostov Region, and the Krasnoyarsk Territory. Along with that, few people under this name reside in Kazakhstan.","The last name was mentioned in manuscripts since the 17th century. Peasant Dmitry Romanovich lived in the Galich eldership in 1640. The Zaporizhian Army Register of 1649 included Cossack Avram Romanovich from the Omelnitskaya Sotnia of the Chyhyryn Regiment, Cossack Artyukh Romanovich from the Irkliiv Sotnia of the Kropyvna Regiment, and Cossack Zakhar Romanovich from the Medvedovskaya Sotnia of the Chyhyryn Regiment. Alexander Mikhaylovich Romanovich was listed as a service noble of the Russian Empire in 1794. In 1848, Mikhail Alexandrovich Romanovich gained the rank of ensign of the 3rd Novorossiysk Dragoon Regiment. Noble Osip Adolfovich Romanovich from the Vilnius Province participated in the Polish revolt. Due to this fact, he was exiled to Siberia in 1864. Citizen Alexey Alexandrovich Romanovich resided in Kaluga in 1907. Alexander Romualdovich Romanovich had the captain rank and served in the Dragoon Lifeguards Regiment in Peterhof in 1909."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Мстислав Романович was born in 1167. She had at least 4 sons and 4 daughters with Mstislav III Boris Prince Of Kiev."},"et":{"1167–":"1167–Surnud","1154–1223":"1154–1223","1175–Male":"1175–Surnud","1177–Male":"1177–Surnud","1181–Male":"1181–Surnud","1183–1245":"1183–1245","1185–Female":"1185–Surnud","1187–1220":"1187–1220","1189–Female":"1189–Surnud","1191–Female":"1191–Surnud","1167–Female":"1167–Surnud","1220":"1220","1187":"1187","1154":"1154","1175":"1175","1185":"1185","1183":"1183","1181":"1181","1191":"1191","ABT 1183":"umbes 1183","ABT 1185":"umbes 1185","ABT 1175":"umbes 1175","ABT 1187":"umbes 1187","ABT 1177":"umbes 1177","1245":"1245","1223":"1223","1167":"1167","ABT 1189":"umbes 1189","1189":"1189","1177":"1177","ABT 1181":"umbes 1181","Abt 1191":"umbes 1191","Smolensk, Smolensk, Russia":"Smolensk, Smolensky Rayon, Smolensk, Russia, Nõukogude Liit"},"fi":{"1167–":"1167–Kuollut","1154–1223":"1154–1223","1175–Male":"1175–Kuollut","1177–Male":"1177–Kuollut","1181–Male":"1181–Kuollut","1183–1245":"1183–1245","1185–Female":"1185–Kuollut","1187–1220":"1187–1220","1189–Female":"1189–Kuollut","1191–Female":"1191–Kuollut","1167–Female":"1167–Kuollut","1220":"1220","1187":"1187","1154":"1154","1175":"1175","1185":"1185","1183":"1183","1181":"1181","1191":"1191","ABT 1183":"noin 1183","ABT 1185":"noin 1185","ABT 1175":"noin 1175","ABT 1187":"noin 1187","ABT 1177":"noin 1177","1245":"1245","1223":"1223","1167":"1167","ABT 1189":"noin 1189","1189":"1189","1177":"1177","ABT 1181":"noin 1181","Abt 1191":"noin 1191","Smolensk, Smo